{"id": "duc04-testb-15:14#42", "contents": "Matthew Wayne Shepard, the gay student who was brutally beaten and left to die alone, was mourned at his funeral by 1,000 people, including many who had never met him. His cousin, Rev. Anne Kitch, delivered a homily that highlighted Shepard's selfless nature, stating that he believed making one person's life better was a success. The service was attended by a packed crowd at St. Mark's Episcopal Church, with overflow attendees listening from a nearby parish hall and Presbyterian church, as well as via an AM radio station broadcast. Shepard's life and tragic death have resonated with the world, inspiring a national response to ensure physical safety for the LGBTQ+ community."}
